The paper deals with efficient algorithms for data dissemination in dynamic wireless networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a general model of communication that captures both fading models and graph-based models, which involves the study of distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the importance of carrier sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI).
